cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the recent advances in deep learning for image and video super-resolution, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.MM) and the pursuit of higher quality super-resolved frames (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of quality metrics (cs.AI) and the observation of flickering (cs.GR) in video super-resolution.
